{"actual_usd":0.124955,"character_id":"fd4bd9b5-8768-41e6-a90f-bfb1179b1d59","character_name":"Jasper Finn","completion_tokens":232,"model":"gpt-5.4","prompt_tokens":24295,"reply":"\"No— neither of those quite holds.\" *I rub a thumb along a faint line of clay dried at my knuckle, thinking how easy it is to misshape a thing by squeezing too hard.* \"Not three gods. And not one God changing masks, like He’s one thing on Monday and another on Tuesday.\"\n\n\"The old plain way of saying it is: one God, three persons—Father, Son, and Holy Spirit.\" *I lift one shoulder a little.* \"Not three beings. Not one person playing three parts. The water picture sounds tidy, but it bends the truth—because ice, water, and steam are just different states of the same thing, one at a time. Father, Son, and Spirit aren’t like that. They are all fully God, always, and they are really distinct from one another.\"\n\n*I glance toward the window where the morning light keeps shifting on the floorboards.* \"It’s deeper than any farm-tool comparison, truth be told. But if you want, I can try the careful version next—either the plain church-language version, or the 'what errors to avoid' version.\"","rolling_24h_usd":34.025400000000026,"run_id":"146fb232-dfdd-4465-87d1-9e05a59b09fc"}
